@Cosmic Smeck I've had it for ~2 days now, so I'll give you my first thoughts. For height wise, it fits fine. My head reaches just to the top of the chair, but the pillow is right in my neck, which feels nice. Width wise, I can feel the lower side bolster things touching my sides, but it doesn't feel tight, or squeezing, just sort of feel support there. The arm rests have lots of movement so I've been able to find a good position for them. The front of the seat has a bit of a ridge, which I can feel in my legs, but I'm assuming that will soften out over time.


Overall I feel the chair is pretty stiff. I came from an Ikea Markus chair, which when I go to sit in again, feels mushy and soft. The reason I wanted a change is because that chair basically has no back support and the seat cushion is just completely gone after 5+ years of use. You can see indention's where I sit and it basically goes straight to the wood/metal below. This chair feels much more supportive and I hope the foam breaks in a bit over time. I wouldn't say it's too hard, as I sat in this for ~12 hours the first day I got it just trying a bunch of different things out while I was working from home. I absolutely love how easy it is to just turn off the lock and basically have a rocking chair/recliner, or drop the back out and lay almost flat. I have a TV mounted right above my desk/monitors, and I'm already really enjoying just laying back and watching TV that way. It will freak you out at first, thinking it's going to tip over, but after doing it a few times and realizing it's still pretty stable, it's nice just knowing you have that option.


So to sum it up, If you are the same size as me, I wouldn't worry about the fit so much, I think you will be fine. Just make sure you understand it's a bit firm and might take some getting used to depending on what your chairs in the past have been, but will also give more support than other older chairs. The quality feels pretty top notch and putting it together by myself wasn't difficult. Let me know if you have any other specific questions and I'll do my best to answer.

