@DBR ___ depends on what you want to spend or what you want in terms of "quality of life" things. So for example, a budget ergonomic office style chair is the Autonomous Ergochair V2, however while the armrests are 4D directional, they do not lock in place aside from up and down, which was a huge no-go for me. This is actually something I liked about my Secretlab chair... The armrests, while way too hard and poorly angled in my opinion, locked in all directions and never moved on me during use. The Ergochair v2 looks like a gust of wind would move the armrests.

