@TheAxelBrown PU Leather doesn't breath because it doesnt have gaps between fibers.  Leather does a little, but not when you sweat as it creates a seal.

Wearing no clothes on a PU chair is definitely something you want to avoid, and it will cause you to sweat a lot even without it being that warm - this feels yuk and will also degrade the pu leather much faster. Honestly even real leather you don't want to do that because even though it does breath a bit, if it is hot and you sweat its going to seal and you will stick. 

PU is GREAT, and good quality variety of it like this one will actually keeps its original color FAR longer than leather, however just don't go on it without clothes, or expect it to be great feeling when hot.
